This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) because it proposes an optimized pipeline architecture on FPGA for accelerating inference of CNNs. It is also likely to belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) because it focuses on accelerating CNNs, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Additionally, it may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) because it proposes a systematic pruning algorithm based on ADMM. It may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) because it addresses the redundancy in model parameters using weight pruning techniques. Finally, it may belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) because it proposes a hardware implementation for accelerating CNNs.
